text: Quercus basaseachicensis is a kind of oak tree in the Fagaceae family. It is believed to be a cross of Quercus rugosa and Quercus depressipes.Quercus basaseachicensis - IUCN Red List It is native to Chihuahua and Durango in Mexico, where there are five known small populations; one in Durango and four in Chihuahua. ==References== Category:Fagales Category:Trees
title: Quercus basaseachicensis
